could really fix the Wizard without unbalancing them.<br>
<br>
We both agreed that adding new spells would be hard. Some form of &quot;Group Friendly&quot; spell would be nice. This is what we came up with. Mana costs/Casting Times/Recast Times are all variable, its the main idea we are talking about. =D<br>
<br>
Name: Blink (or Gate Trigger)<br>
Target: Self Only<br>
Mana Cost: 220<br>
Casting Time: 8.0<br>
Effect: Basically, a buff for a high risk area. CR in Fear comes to mind. It works like a Death Pact line of spells, (% chance of spell going off, at a bubble of life or there abouts) only instead of a heal its an instant cast 'Gate' (hopefully youre not bound in Fear =p~ ) Would be based off CHA or any stat you wanted really. Nice little &quot;Get ouf of Jail Free&quot; Card.<br>
<br>
-You feel your body shift.<br>
-Soandso's image blurs.<br>
<br>
Name: Displacement (or Portal Trigger)<br>
Target: Group Spell<br>
Mana Cost: 480<br>
Casting Time: 12.0<br>
Effect: A group blink spell.<br>
<br>
-You feel displaced.<br>
-Soandso's image shifts drastically.<br>
<br>
<br>
Thats not where the true fix is however. That just lets us be a little bit more group friendly, and actually have a buff worth a damn =p~<br>
<br>
Warriors are the &quot;Pure Tank Class&quot; as far as damage is concerned. Wizards should be the &quot;Pure Caster Class&quot; when it comes to damage. Thats our reasoning for the following.<br>
<br>
Wizard Disciplines. Nothing too fancy or insane, but something to set us apart from the rest of the casting classes (without overpowering us.)<br>
<br>
These are far from finished concepts, but you'll get the idea.<br>
<br>
Name: Racing Mind<br>
Level: 55<br>
Refresh Time: 40 Minutes.<br>
Duration: 24 seconds.<br>
Effect: For the duration, mana regeneration is increased 8-10 times. Stacks with all current buffs (if possible).<br>
<br>
-Diison is gripped by overwhelming concentration!<br>
<br>
Name: Evasion (aka: Bouncing Wizards!)<br>
Level: 56<br>
Refresh Time: 20 Minutes.<br>
Duration: 8 seconds.<br>
Effect: For the duration, each time the wizard is struck at, a small shadowstep+concussion spell is instantly cast on the target striking.<br>
<br>
-Diison's body shifts from vision!<br>
<br>
Name: Intensify<br>
Level: 57<br>
Refresh Time: 30 Minutes.<br>
Duration: One Cast.<br>
Effect: The next time a Wizard casts, the effects will be tripled. Range, Damage, Effect, Duration. (does not work with self only spells).<br>
<br>
-Diison's hands are bathed in mana!<br>
<br>
Name: Focus<br>
Level: 58<br>
Refresh Time: 1h 15m<br>
Duration: 30 seconds<br>
Effect: During the duration, random bonus spells are cast at the target. Spell types will be determined by those casting (DD's will result random DD's, PB-AE's would result random PB-AE's). These extra spells would cost no mana, and would normally be below level 50.<br>
<br>
-Diison's eyes gleam with a sense of focus!<br>
<br>
Name: Ethereal<br>
Level: 59<br>
Refresh: 60 minutes<br>
Duration: 12 seconds<br>
Effect: This gives the Wizard a 12 second Divine Aura type spell, with an increase in mana regeneration (but nothing major).<br>
<br>
-Diison shifts into the Ethereal!<br>
<br>
Name: Fury<br>
Level: 60<br>
Refresh Time: 1h 30m<br>
Duration: 12 seconds<br>
Effect: Basically removes casting time completely from all spells. (sets all casting times of spells to 0.1, instant casts). Does *not* however, remove recast times.<br>
<br>
-Diison's body is consumed in waves of mana!<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
There was also some talk of givings wizards 57+ Double Cast. Basically a percentage chance based on Dex, that two spells would go off in a single cast. Cast Draught, and have it double hit every once in a while. We thought this might push the whole idea over the edge tho, and it didnt meet the &quot;original idea&quot; category (double backstab). <br>
<br>
None of those, we thought, were TOO terribly bad. It would definitly attract people to play wizards again, without overpowering them or adding a slew of new spells. Fury sounds bad.. but thats what a level 60 Sorceror should be. And think about the aggro you'd build up, It would have to be used very carefully in specific instances, (or when you knew you were going to die anyway, and wanted to empty your mana bar). THAT is the main point. To often wizards get to cast a spell once, get resisted, (even lures heh) cause massive aggro and die. At least this way, as we are getting pummelled we are doing our part.<br>
<br>
Just thought I'd share with you guys. Something to put on our Wish Lists i guess. =p <br>
